# Angular Blog CMS Rules

## Component Structure
- Always separate HTML, CSS, and TypeScript files
- Use standalone components with explicit imports
- Follow the naming convention: `component-name.component.ts/html/css`

## State Management
- Use Angular Signals for reactive state
- Services should use `providedIn: 'root'` for singleton instances
- Computed values should use `computed()` for derived state

## Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Keep component-specific styles in separate `.css` files
- Use CSS custom properties for theme-able values

## SEO Optimization
- Always set meta tags using SEOService
- Include structured data for blog posts
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy (h1, h2, h3, etc.)

## Code Organization
- Models in `src/app/models/`
- Services in `src/app/services/`
- Components in `src/app/components/`
- Lazy load routes for better performance

## TypeScript
- Use strict mode
- Define proper interfaces for all data structures
- Avoid `any` type - use proper types or `unknown`
- Use enums for fixed sets of values

## Best Practices
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Use dependency injection for services
- Implement proper error handling
- Use async/await for asynchronous operations
- Follow Angular style guide conventions
